        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "SQA acceptance criteria — commercial FEA code with documented V&V",
        "description": "The FEA solver (Ansys Mechanical 2022 R2) must be a commercially released code with documented software quality assurance procedures, version-controlled input decks, and a traceable audit trail of model revisions. Acceptance is met if the solver release notes, regression test suite results, and input-deck version history are available in the submission package."
      },
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical 2022 R2 is a commercially released, ISO 9001-certified FEA platform. Input decks are version-controlled under Git (SHA hashes recorded in the submission). Regression test suite results for the structural mechanics module are provided by Ansys Inc. as part of the release documentation. FDA OSEL internal SQA checklist (SQA-CHK-2023-04) was completed and signed by the lead analyst. Achieved Gradation 3 because an independent code-to-code comparison against Abaqus 2021 was also performed for the stiffness QoI, confirming numerical equivalence within 0.4%."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/factor/ncv-cou1",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/ac/ncv-cou1",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Numerical code verification acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Solver must reproduce analytical or manufactured solutions for linear elastic beam bending and contact problems to within 1% relative error. Patch test pass documented in the submission."
      },
      "rationale": "The Ansys Mechanical structural solver was verified against the Timoshenko beam analytical solution for a cantilever under end load (error 0.31%) and a Hertzian contact patch test (error 0.18%). Both results are documented in the NCV report (NCV-RPT-2023-07). Required Gradation 2 is met; no higher gradation was pursued because the physics are well within the solver's validated operating range."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/factor/disc-error-cou1",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/ac/disc-error-cou1",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Discretization error acceptance criteria — mesh convergence study",
        "description": "A three-level mesh refinement study (coarse/medium/fine, element edge length ratio 2:1 between successive levels) must demonstrate that QoI values (stiffness, yield force) change by less than 2% between medium and fine meshes. Richardson extrapolation GCI must be reported and must be below 1% for the fine mesh."
      },
      "rationale": "Mesh convergence was assessed across three refinement levels (coarse: ~18 k elements; medium: ~72 k elements; fine: ~290 k elements). Stiffness changed by 1.1% from medium to fine; yield force changed by 0.8%. Richardson extrapolation GCI for the fine mesh was 0.6% for stiffness and 0.5% for yield force. Results documented in MESH-CONV-RPT-2023-09. Gradation 3 achieved because the formal GCI protocol was applied and all QoIs are below the 2% threshold."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/factor/nse-cou1",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/ac/nse-cou1",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Numerical solver error acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Iterative solver residuals must converge to below 1e-6 for all load steps. Force-displacement curve must exhibit monotonic loading without spurious oscillations. Energy balance error must be below 0.1% per load increment."
      },
      "rationale": "All 11 simulation runs converged with residuals below 1e-8. Energy balance errors were below 0.05% across all load increments. No spurious oscillations were observed in any force-displacement curve. Solver log files are archived in the submission package. Gradation 2 is met; no nonlinear iteration convergence issues were encountered."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/factor/use-error-cou1",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
